  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Community Worker",
  "description": "<p><strong>Community Engagement and Relationship Building</strong></p><ul><li>Build and maintain relationships with community members in public rental blocks through door-knocking and conversations.</li><li>Mobilise and empower community members to use their strengths and interests to contribute for community initiatives.</li></ul><p><strong>Resource and Partnership Management</strong></p><ul><li>Secure and manage resources including volunteers,and partnerships with varied organisations such as grassroots and corporates.</li></ul><p><strong>Collaboration with SSA and Community Centric Casework Support</strong></p><ul><li>Work with other social service agencies to support families with community-centric casework that addresses individual and family crises.</li></ul><p><strong>Team Leadership and Supervision</strong></p><ul><li>Oversee the team’s workplan and projects as assigned, and guide team members in project management and community work practice.</li><li>Oversee and guide team members in achieving the team’s community development workplan and key performance indicators.</li></ul><p><strong>General Duties</strong></p><ul><li>Perform any other responsibilities and duties assigned.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Social Work or related field.  Preferably 3-5 years’ experience in community work practice or related field.</li><li>Experience in leading a team is a plus (leadership or supervisory experience preferred).</li><li>Experience in arts-based facilitation or community theatre is a plus.</li><li>Possesses a keen interest in working with less resourced families, children and youth.</li><li>Strong organisational and time management skills, with an ability to manage multiple projects effectively.</li><li>An excellent team player with good interpersonal and listening skills.</li><li>Motivated towards learning and professional development.</li><li>Flexible and open to adapt to organisational changes or ground concerns.</li><li>Good writing skills and comfortable with data collation for reporting purposes.</li><li>Proficiency in Microsoft Office.</li><li>Willing and able to work on some weekday evenings and weekends.</li></ul>",
